<article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-950 sm:text-4xl">Cookie Policy</h1>
  <p class="mt-4 text-slate-700">
    This policy explains what cookies we use, why we use them, and how you can control them.
  </p>
  <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">Last updated: {{ privacy.lastUpdated | dateDmy }}</p>

  <div class="panel mt-8 p-6 sm:p-8">
    <div class="space-y-6 text-slate-800 [&_h2]:text-2xl [&_h2]:font-semibold [&_h2]:tracking-tight [&_li]:leading-7 [&_p]:leading-7 [&_ul]:list-disc [&_ul]:space-y-1 [&_ul]:pl-6">
      <section>
        <h2>1) What Are Cookies?</h2>
        <p>
          Cookies are small text files stored on your device. Some are required for the website to function, while
          others are optional and help us understand site usage.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>2) Cookie Categories We Use</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Strictly necessary:</strong> required for core functionality, security, and preference controls.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>3) Consent</h2>
        <p>
          Because we currently use only strictly necessary cookies, there is no analytics cookie opt-in flow active.
        </p>
        <p>
          You can still open cookie settings at any time:
        </p>
        <button data-open-cookie-preferences="true" type="button" class="inline-flex items-center rounded-lg bg-slate-900 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-white transition hover:bg-blue-700">
          Cookie settings
        </button>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>4) Analytics Provider</h2>
        <p>
          We use Cloudflare Web Analytics for high-level traffic reporting. This policy will be updated if we add
          any optional analytics tools in the future.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>5) Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about this cookie policy can be sent to
          <a class="text-blue-700 hover:underline" href="mailto:{{ privacy.contactEmail }}">{{ privacy.contactEmail }}</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</article>
